1934;;Twenty Million Sweethearts;;American;;Ray Enright;;Ginger Rogers, Dick Powell, Ted Fio Rito;;comedy, musical;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twenty_Million_Sweethearts;;Agent Russell Edward 'Rush' Blake (Pat O'Brien) is able to promote the singing tenor waiter Buddy Clayton (Dick Powell) as a major radio star whilst Buddy's wife Peggy Cornell (Ginger Rogers) loses out. In the end, Peggy does not lose Buddy to his "twenty million sweethearts" - his female fans.[1]